# Plan: Animate Links with Header Color Cycle

## Context
The site's headers use a `.colorful` class that runs the `header` keyframe animation, cycling through four pastel hues (purple → pink → blue-grey → teal). Links currently have a static vivid blue (`hsl(225, 100%, 40%)`) with a matching wavy underline. The user wants links to animate with the same color palette as the headers.

## Approach

Edit `css/style.css` to:

1. **Add the `header` animation to `a, a:visited`** — this applies the same 5s infinite color cycle.
2. **Also animate `text-decoration-color`** — the wavy underline should cycle in sync. The existing `header` keyframes only animate `color`, so create a new `link` keyframe that animates both `color` and `text-decoration-color` through the same four hues. Apply this new animation to `a, a:visited` instead.

### New keyframes (add to style.css)

```css
@-webkit-keyframes link {
    0%   { color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%); text-decoration-color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%); }
    25%  { color: hsl(330, 39%, 67%); text-decoration-color: hsl(330, 39%, 67%); }
    50%  { color: hsl(229, 25%, 64%); text-decoration-color: hsl(229, 25%, 64%); }
    75%  { color: hsl(185, 35%, 67%); text-decoration-color: hsl(185, 35%, 67%); }
    to   { color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%); text-decoration-color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%); }
}
@keyframes link {
    0%   { color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%); text-decoration-color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%); }
    25%  { color: hsl(330, 39%, 67%); text-decoration-color: hsl(330, 39%, 67%); }
    50%  { color: hsl(229, 25%, 64%); text-decoration-color: hsl(229, 25%, 64%); }
    75%  { color: hsl(185, 35%, 67%); text-decoration-color: hsl(185, 35%, 67%); }
    to   { color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%); text-decoration-color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%); }
}
```

### Updated `a, a:visited` rule

```css
a, a:visited {
    color: hsl(272, 20%, 58%);
    text-underline-position: under;
    text-decoration: wavy underline hsl(272, 20%, 58%);
    -webkit-animation: link 5s ease forwards infinite;
    animation: link 5s ease forwards infinite;
}
```

## Critical file
- `css/style.css` — lines 137–141 (the `a, a:visited` block) and the keyframes section

## Verification
Open `index.html` in a browser and confirm:
- All links cycle through the same four pastel colors as the `h2.colorful` headings
- The wavy underline color matches the text color as it animates
- Visited links behave the same way

